description:
&lt;p&gt;Leicester City, West Leicestershire, and East Leicestershire and Rutland CCGs commission and provide health and care services for over a million people in Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland (LLR) and have a combined budget of c. £1.5 billion. The population and budget broadly divide equally between the three CCGs. The combined total of Primary Care Networks is 25. The CCGs are accountable for all strategic commissioning and contract management arrangements for the provider contracts. The three LLR CCGs work collaboratively with the local authorities in addition to the borough/district councils in Leicestershire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for the recruitment of 2.6 WTE Medicines Optimisation Pharmacists to join the Medicines Optimisation Team across Leicester Leicestershire and Rutland CCGs to support facilitate and deliver the Medicines Optimisation Agenda&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Medicines Optimisation Team you will support and contribute to the development of medicines optimisation related projects and initiatives to safely and effectively deliver the Medicines Optimisation agenda across Leicester Leicestershire and Rutland&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
